<title>USA: DCI Telecommunications explores spin-off.</title>
<headline>DCI Telecommunications explores spin-off.</headline>
<dateline>FAIRFIELD, Conn. 1996-10-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>DCI Telecommunications said Tuesday that as a result of a recently concluded agreement it reacquired all its prior interest in a joint venture with Telephonica International, thus paving the way to proceed with negotiations on a potential business combination with American Cash Card Corporation (AMCASH).</p>
<p>Joseph Murphy, DCI President, issued a statement saying the agreement &quot;simplifies what could have been a rather complicated arrangement.&quot;</p>
<p>Once finalized, the president of AMCASH would become the president of DCI with Murphy becoming chairman.</p>
<p>DCI said it is continuing to work towards its announced acquisition of Muller Media and should completed it shortly.</p>
